goals.question: What is the distribution of body mass across different penguin species?
goals.visualization: box plot of Body_Mass__g_ by Species
goals.rationale: This will help us understand if there are any significant differences in body mass between different penguin species.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between beak length and beak depth?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of Beak_Length__mm_ vs Beak_Depth__mm_
goals.rationale: This will help us understand if there is a relationship between the two variables and if they can be used interchangeably in analysis.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flipper length across different penguin species?
goals.visualization: box plot of Flipper_Length__mm_ by Species
goals.rationale: This will help us understand if there are any significant differences in flipper length between different penguin species.

goals.question: What is the distribution of body mass by gender?
goals.rationale: This will help us understand if there are any significant differences in body mass between male and female penguins.

goals.question: What is the distribution of beak length across different islands?
goals.visualization: box plot of Beak_Length__mm_ by Island
goals.rationale: This will help us understand if there are any significant differences in beak length between penguins from different islands.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='Species', y='Body_Mass__g_', data=data)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of body mass across different penguin species?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='Beak_Length__mm_', y='Beak_Depth__mm_', data=data)
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between beak length and beak depth?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Beak Length (mm)')
    plt.ylabel('Beak Depth (mm)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Island'] = data['Island'].astype('category')
    data['Beak_Length__mm_'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Beak_Length__mm_'], errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x='Island', y='Beak_Length__mm_', data=data)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of beak length across different islands?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
